    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Muruaga</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April
                                        4, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In confirmation of his last communication of March 20 last, the
                            undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of Spain,
                            has the honor to notify the honorable Secretary of State that, according
                            to official and reliable information, a filibustering expedition,
                            commanded by Gonzalo de Quesada, secretary of the Cuban Revolutionary
                            Junta, and a naturalized American citizen, is on the point of setting
                            out from Tampa, Fla., for the Island of Cuba.</p>
                <p>The undersigned avails, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. de Muruaga.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
